Well, this is V2 of my map, it should be the last version, but some people amy coem up with new problems, and if so, I'll make only one more version, especially becasue i had to stop the vvis on the compile (1 hour and only on 1...2..) anyway, the changes

1. Thanks to WhaThe for pointing out there was a problem with my awsome jail, I've improved on it immensly. There are now teleporterts on each floor to teleport to the other floors (still in jail) smgs on top floor, pistols on second, nothing on bottom. Also, I've added on bottom floor a button to kill yourself and everyone on floor, opeing up the floor itself, and the top floor contains a crush button, causing a huge block to come down and crush the top two floors and its inhabitants.

2.I managed to get a working screen in the credits room at end, and I replaced the buyzone with a large pile of weapons and improved the teleporter part there. It now teleports you to the jail outside part.

3.Added a few obstacles in final boost tunnel and you no longer have to jump at end of it, you'll have to wait and see what it's like...

4.More variation at start, glass tunnel, better looking wall and my new map symbol, looks pretty good. 

In whole, I'm pleased with this version, a few problems along the way but it got there. Thanks again to WhaThe for pointing out the jail problem.

I think this is my best map yet, it's taken me about a week to get everything running smoothly(ish) on the map and I'm very pleased with the outcome. 

fewnotes:
1.My jail is something not seen in most surf maps now. 3 floors, fall off in each surf section, you are teleported to one of the 3 floors. If you reach the end and teleport to the jail, you can choose to either release everyone or simply open up all floors to the spike pit


2.There are two huge towers at the start and end, simply jump when your in, it's great, seriously! I'm gonna make things like that a constant in my surf maps from now on

3.I don't know if anyone else will have the problem, but at the end by the side of jail, I got stuck halfway up the ladder then sort of juddered up. Thing is, when I started the map again, it didnt have a problem, so there shudnt b a problem lol

4.few plans for v2 already. hope to have my name scrolling in dynamic lights, very hard and long time to work on that, and it may not work... in the jail I plan to put certain weapons on different floors as a sort of reward for getting to certain further sections, and to help distinguish between each floor. smgs on top floor, pistols on second, nothing in bottom naturally. I also plan to change the random laser in the middle of the last part to something else cool, any ideas, PM please, ill mention you in credits then, ty

Hey! Good to see you found my map...

Some tips for first timers:
1. Surf Clockwise around the rings.
2. Brown ramps push you out, white ramps push you inward.
3. Behind the brown blocks up top are secret areas. ;)
4. There is no way out of jail, except death.
5. The sides of the platforms in jail teleport to each other.

ENJOY!!!
~Chaos Theory~

Change log from beta3:
1. Changed a few textures in the Ring area.
2. Changed / Optimized jail lighting.
3. Removed the fences in the Ring area.
4. Added some lamps and lights for nice effects.

This is my first map release, and really the first map I've made as well, though it's gone through numerous versions to get to the state it's in now.  It's the first idea I had for a map, that is a setting where the sun is setting, the lights have just come on, and you're in that in between area between light and dark.

This was designed to be a combat map, but since it was requested, I've included an _njv version as well.  There are three possible places where you can "end", but only two jail camps.  I hope to come back to this map another time, perhaps after my next release to add some secret areas and touch up on some of the content.

I hope you all enjoy it ~

This map was made by me Pwn3r1001 with some influence from surf_matrix_v8 because of the secret areas and portals. If you think this map is all about suicidal surfing dodging lasers, ducking gun fire, speeding through portals of fiery rings well your right it does have that. But this is mostly about finding secrets in the map that lead you to places allowing you to have an advantage such as seeing the enemy without them seeing you. If you try to surf the map and quickly get to an obvious location with water and guns and a teleportal than you are most likely missing a lot of areas you can go to. Anyways this map is more than you think, and yes looks can be deceiving. Have fun and expect to see it on my server soon
